    slug: "drug-free-housing-west-palm-beach",
    title: "Finding Drug-Free Housing in West Palm Beach: A Complete Guide",
    excerpt:
      "Stable, substance-free housing is the foundation of lasting recovery. Here's a full guide to drug-free housing options in West Palm Beach, what to look for, and red flags to avoid.",
    date: "2026-03-25",
    readTime: "7 min",
    category: "Education",
    author: "Ocean Breeze Recovery Housing",
    content: "Finding stable, substance-free housing is one of the most critical needs in early recovery. Whether you've just completed treatment, recently left an active using environment, or are simply looking to get away from people and places connected to your addiction, drug-free housing provides the foundation everything else is built on.\n\n## What Is Drug-Free Housing?\n\nDrug-free housing is residential housing where all residents have agreed — and are held accountable — to living without drugs or alcohol. This includes:\n\n- Zero tolerance for any substance use on or off the property\n- Random drug and alcohol screening\n- A management structure that enforces the agreement\n- A community of residents with shared commitments to sobriety\n\n## Why Housing Environment Matters in Recovery\n\nYour environment is one of the strongest predictors of relapse. Research shows that people who return to environments where drugs are available — with people who use, in homes where using happened — relapse at dramatically higher rates than those who move into substance-free housing.\n\nThis is why the housing piece of recovery is not a luxury or an afterthought. It is fundamental.\n\n## Drug-Free Housing Options in West Palm Beach\n\nWest Palm Beach and Palm Beach County have a range of drug-free housing options:\n\n**Sober living homes**: Privately operated, community-based substance-free housing with peer support and house rules. Most are gender-specific. Costs range from $200–$500/week.\n\n**Oxford Houses**: Democratically run, self-supporting sober living homes. Costs are typically lower. No professional management on-site.\n\n**Halfway houses**: Government or nonprofit funded, often for justice-involved individuals. Lower cost, less autonomy.\n\n**Transitional housing programs**: Attached to specific treatment or court programs. May have clinical programming integrated.\n\n## What to Look For in Drug-Free Housing\n\n- Drug screening (random, regular) — critical\n- Live-in management or on-site presence\n- Transparent house rules with enforcement\n- Community of recovering residents\n- Proximity to recovery meetings, work, and support services\n\n## Red Flags to Avoid\n\n- No drug testing or honor-system sobriety\n- Overcrowded homes with no management oversight\n- Vague or unenforced rules\n- Transient population with high turnover\n- No employment expectations\n\n## Ocean Breeze: Drug-Free Housing in West Palm Beach\n\nOcean Breeze Recovery Housing is a men's sober living home in West Palm Beach providing structured, drug-free housing at $275/week. All-inclusive. Live-in manager Kevin Smith. Random drug screening. Employment required.\n\nCall (561) 646-7097 to check availability.",
